In case of @ramsey_gillig 's issue, we require `pidmode` to be `host` so container will have access to host's PIDs. But, if it's empty, it'll lead to failure of GPU usage check. 

Here are what you can do if you ran executor using `docker-compose.app.yml`: 
- Please kill all executor services using `docker compose down -f docker-compose.app.yml`
- Run executor services again using `docker compose up -d`

LMK if you have any questions.

Minimum stake weight on mainnet, to be able to set weights as a validator, is 1000.  It's calculated as `tao * .18 + alpha`, and could be:
o 18000 TAO
o 1000 alpha tokens
o Some combination such that total stake weight is 1000 or more.
If you don't meet the requirements, your validator will not be able to set weights.  If it does not set weights within the activity interval, its ACTIVE flag will be set to FALSE and it'll likely be deregistered by incoming registrations.

More here: https://docs.bittensor.com/validators/#requirements-for-validation

These are *minimums*.  To remain in consensus, your validator needs to be on part with the majority of stake in the subnet.  This means that the *actual* stake weight you'll need is usually much higher than 1000.
